A prism is constructed so that its vertical edges are parallel to the $z$-axis.  Its cross-section is a square of side length 10.

[asy]
import three;

size(180);
currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H;

A = (1,1,0);
B = (1,-1,0);
C = (-1,-1,0);
D = (-1,1,0);
E = A + (0,0,1);
F = B + (0,0,3);
G = C + (0,0,4);
H = D + (0,0,2);

draw(surface(E--F--G--H--cycle),gray(0.7),nolight);
draw(E--F--G--H--cycle);
draw(A--E);
draw(B--F);
draw(C--G,dashed);
draw(D--H);
draw(B--A--D);
draw(B--C--D,dashed);
[/asy]

The prism is then cut by the plane $4x - 7y + 4z = 25.$  Find the maximal area of the cross-section.

inference:
The cross-section is a quadrilateral, which can be divided into two triangles by a diagonal.  Let the endpoints of this diagonal be $(x_1,y_1,z_1)$ and $(x_2,y_2,z_2).$  Then the area of the quadrilateral is
\[\frac{1}{2} \left| \begin{pmatrix} x_1 & y_1 & 1 \\ x_2 & y_2 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \end{pmatrix} \right| = \frac{1}{2} |x_1 y_2 - x_2 y_1|.\]Since $(x_1,y_1,z_1)$ and $(x_2,y_2,z_2)$ lie on the plane $4x - 7y + 4z = 25,$
\begin{align*}
4x_1 - 7y_1 + 4z_1 &= 25, \\
4x_2 - 7y_2 + 4z_2 &= 25.
\end{align*}Then $4z_1 = 25 - 4x_1 + 7y_1$ and $4z_2 = 25 - 4x_2 + 7y_2,$ so
\[\frac{1}{2} |x_1 y_2 - x_2 y_1| = \frac{1}{2} \left| x_1 \left( \frac{25 - 4x_2 + 7y_2}{4} \right) - x_2 \left( \frac{25 - 4x_1 + 7y_1}{4} \right) \right| = \frac{1}{8} |7x_1 y_2 - 7x_2 y_1|.\]We want to maximize this expression subject to the constraint that $(x_1,y_1)$ and $(x_2,y_2)$ lie on the square.

[asy]
unitsize (0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, P, Q;

A = (-5,5);
B = (5,5);
C = (5,-5);
D = (-5,-5);
P = (-3,3);
Q = (4,-4);

draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);
draw(P--Q);

label("$x_1$", P, NW);
label("$y_1$", P, SW);
label("$x_2$", Q, SE);
label("$y_2$", Q, NE);
[/asy]

Let $(x_1,y_1)$ be in the first quadrant.  Then $(x_2,y_2)$ is in the third quadrant, and we can write $x_1 = 5 - a,$ $y_1 = 5 - b,$ $x_2 = -5 + c,$ and $y_2 = -5 + d,$ where $a,$ $b,$ $c,$ and $d$ are nonnegative.  Then
\[\frac{1}{8} |7x_1 y_2 - 7x_2 y_1| = \frac{7}{8} |(5 - a)(-5 + d) - (-5 + c)(5 - b)|.\]Expanding, we get
\[\frac{7}{8} |25 - 5a + 5d - ad + 25 - 5c + 5b - bc|.\]We want to maximize this expression.  Since $a,$ $b,$ $c,$ and $d$ are nonnegative, the maximum value occurs when $a = b = c = d = 5.$  Then the maximum area is
\[\frac{7}{8} |25 - 5 \cdot 5 + 5 \cdot 5 - 5 \cdot 5 + 25 - 5 \cdot 5 + 5 \cdot 5 - 5 \cdot 5| = \boxed{25}.\]Final Answer: $\boxed{25}$. I hope it is correct.

